---
// about.astro - About Languages 4 page
// Mission-driven page showcasing leadership, values, and company story
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import PDFDownloadModal from '../components/PDFDownloadModal.astro';
import TeamMemberModal from '../components/TeamMemberModal.astro';
import ArticleCard from '../components/ArticleCard.astro';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';

// Fetch specific articles for Core Values showcase
const allArticles = await getCollection('whatarel4');

const coreValuesArticles = [
  allArticles.find(a => a.slug === 'pillar-3-innovative-tech-in-indigenous-language-revitalization-at-languages-4'),
  allArticles.find(a => a.slug === 'languages-4-core-value-language-sovereignty-the-first-piller-of-languages-4'),
  allArticles.find(a => a.slug === 'how-language-sovereignty-trustworthiness-and-innovation-define-languages-4')
].filter(Boolean); // Remove any undefined articles
---

<MainLayout 
  title="About Languages 4 - Mission & Leadership"
  description="Languages 4 is dedicated to Indigenous language reclamation and advancing language sovereignty. Learn about our mission, leadership team, and commitment to community-driven language revitalization."
  image="/images/about-social-share.jpg"
>

<!-- Hero: Mission Statement -->
<section class="relative min-h-[60vh] bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-900 via-primary-800 to-primary-900 flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden px-4 py-20">
  <!-- Background decoration -->
  <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10">
    <div class="absolute top-0 left-1/4 w-96 h-96 bg-accent-600 rounded-full blur-3xl"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 right-1/4 w-96 h-96 bg-[#74a892] rounded-full blur-3xl"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="container mx-auto max-w-5xl relative z-10 text-center">
    <span class="inline-block text-xs md:text-sm font-bold tracking-[2px] text-white/80 bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm px-4 py-2 mb-6 rounded">OUR MISSION</span>
    
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-medium text-white mb-8 leading-tight">
      Indigenous Language Reclamation<br/>& Language Sovereignty
    </h1>
    
    <div class="prose prose-lg md:prose-xl prose-invert mx-auto [&_strong]:text-white [&_strong]:font-bold">
      <p class="text-white/90 text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Languages 4 is dedicated to Indigenous language reclamation and advancing language sovereignty by <strong>following the lead of communities</strong> to revitalize, protect, and sustain their ancestral languages. Language is more than words—it is knowledge, identity, and cultural continuity.
      </p>
      
      <p class="text-white/90 text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed mb-6">
        We stand in solidarity with global movements for language rights and land back, recognizing the historical injustices that led to language loss. <strong>Indigenous peoples must be at the forefront</strong> of their own language reclamation efforts, determining how their languages are taught, shared, and preserved.
      </p>
      
      <p class="text-white/90 text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed">
        Languages 4 provides scalable, accessible, and community-driven educational tools and technologies, ensuring that all language materials remain <strong>fully owned and controlled by the communities we serve</strong>. Our role is not to lead but to support, strengthen, and amplify Indigenous language revitalization.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Our Story -->
<section class="relative py-16 md:py-24 bg-white overflow-hidden">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 md:px-8 lg:pr-24 max-w-6xl">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl font-medium text-primary-900 mb-6">
        Our Story
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-lg md:prose-xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-neutral-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Languages 4 was founded on the principle that <strong>Indigenous peoples must lead their own language reclamation</strong>. Our work began with the Wahta Mohawks in Ontario and has since expanded, always ensuring communities retain full ownership of their language resources.
      </p>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Founder Tim O'Hagan transitioned from teaching English in Japan to working on educational software creation, landing on Indigenous language project development with the Chickasaw, Navajo, and Ojibwe Nations at Rosetta Stone, before launching Languages 4 to make language learning more <strong>affordable, scalable, and community driven</strong>.
      </p>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Tim's sister, Lorelei, Director of Community Engagement, brings two decades of experience in relationship management and community organizing, along with a deep personal connection to language learning and their shared Indigenous heritage. Their great-great aunts were survivors of the Carlisle Indian Boarding School, and their grandmother, Bettie, was a registered member of the Sisseton Wahpeton Oyate Dakota Tribe. <strong>Their family's journey of reconnection fuels the mission of Languages 4.</strong>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

